  <summary>6/16/1987--Introduced.
Amends the Internal Revenue Code to: (1) increase from 25 percent to 80 percent the income tax deduction for the health insurance costs of a self-employed individual; and (2) set a standard by which the health plan of a self-employed individual will be treated with respect to the nondiscrimination requirements applicable to certain employee benefit plans.</summary>
